Claims CLAIMS  What is claimed is 1. A method comprising: receiving, at a remote management platform, a recorded audio message from a first communication device, wherein the first communication device has a default grouping with a set of additional communication devices; and wherein the first communication device includes a cellular networking component capable of connecting the first communication device to a cellular network; identifying, at the remote management platform, the set of additional communication devices associated with the default grouping; and transmitting, from the remote management platform, the recorded audio message to the set of additional communication devices. 2. The method of claim 1, further comprising: receiving a request to create a customized grouping by adding an additional communication device to the default grouping; and creating an entry in a routing table within the remote management platform so any recorded audio message received after the entry is added will be routed to the default grouping and the additional communication device. 3. The method of claim 2, wherein the additional communication device is a bot capable of processing natural language commands and generating a response. 4. The method of claim 2, wherein the request to create the customized grouping occurs from a voice command recorded from the first communication device or a communication device in the set of additional communication devices. 5. The method of claim 1, wherein the default grouping is created at a factory when the communication devices are manufactured. 6. The method of claim 1, wherein the first communication device and the set of additional communications devices automatically pair upon initialization via a local communication network and generate a linking request that is automatically sent to the remote management platform to create the default grouping by creating an entry in a routing table at the remote management platform. 7. The method of claim 6, further comprising identifying communication devices within that are present upon initialization and within a distance of a short-range signal generated by one of the communication devices and wherein the linking request includes a device ID of each of the communication devices that were present upon initialization. 8. The method of claim 7, wherein at least one of the set of additional communication devices include a cellular communications component capable of connecting directly with a cellular network. 9. A remote management platform comprising: a processor; a database having stored thereon multiple group profiles, wherein each of the multiple group profiles include communication profiles identifying communication devices within a group of communication devices associated with that profile a pairing module configured to - receive a grouping request generated upon an initial activation of a communication device; and create an entry within a routing table based, at least in part, on information within the grouping request associating multiple communication devices together so that recorded audio messages received from any one of the communication devices are automatically routed to the remaining communication devices according to the entry within the routing table; and, a group management module configured to - receive a modification request from one of the multiple communication devices; and 

 update the entry in the routing table to include an additional communication device or to remove at least one of the communication devices from the group. 10. The remote management platform of claim 9, further comprising a natural language processor to analyze the recorded audio messages. 11. The remote management platform of claim 10, wherein the natural language processor monitors the recorded audio messages for directives and the remote management platform further comprises: a message conversion module that, upon generates a modified message based, at least in part, on the directive identified by the natural language processor; and a routing module to route the modified message to a destination. 12. The remote management platform of claim 11, wherein the directive is an implicit directive to which a bot could respond, the destination is the bot, and the modified message is also generated by the message conversion module to comply with a communication protocol of the bot. 13. The remote management platform of claim 12, further comprising: an identification module to receive responses from the bot and identify the group for routing; and the routing module routes responses from the bot to the group identified by the identification module. 14. The remote management platform of claim 11, wherein the directive is an explicit directive identifying a bot and the destination is the bot. 15. A method comprising: generating, at a communications device, a registration request upon initial activation of the communication device, wherein the communication device is authorized to be used on a cellular network; 

 wherein the cellular network is used to transmit an activation signal from the communication device to a cloud-based management platform running on one or more servers; and wherein the cloud-based management platform automatically associates, upon activation and based on a factory setting, the communication device with a group of additional communication devices identified by the factory setting; and at the communications device, recording an audio message that upon completion of the recording is then transmitted via the cellular network to the cloud-based management platform, wherein the cloud-based management platform identifies the group of additional communication devices and automatically transmits the recorded audio message to each of the additional communication devices. 16. The method of claim 15, wherein the factory setting used by the cloud-based management platform associate the communication device with the additional communication devices includes an identification number of the communication device and additional communication numbers of the additional communication devices. 17. The method of claim 16, wherein the identification number of the communication device and additional identification numbers of the additional communication devices share a common portion. 18. The method of claim 15, wherein the additional communication devices include one or more bots, voice assistants, or internet of things (IoT) devices. 19. The method of claim 15, wherein the communication device includes a cellular communication component capable of connecting directly with a cellular communication network without an intermediate device. 20. The method of claim 15, wherein the communication device includes a natural language processor to detect implicit directives, explicit directives, group directives and bot directives and route the recorded audio message according to an identified meaning.
